    "title": "Sleep, Dream, Wake",
    "description": "&quot;As a dream when one awaketh.&quot;\n–Psalms. LXXIII. 20.\n\n&quot;Dreaming is not merely an act of communication; it is also an aesthetic activity, a game of the imagination, a game that is a value in itself.&quot;\n–Milan Kundera\n\n&quot;First organize the inner, then organize the outer. First organize the great, then organize the small. First organize yourself, and then organize others.&quot;\n–Zhuge Liang\n\n&quot;We are such stuff\nAs dreams are made on, and our little life\nIs rounded with a sleep.&quot;\n–William Shakespeare, The Tempest \n\n&quot;Imagine there's no countries,\nIt isnt hard to do,\nNothing to kill or die for,\nNo religion too,\nImagine all the people\nliving life in peace...\nYou may say I'm a dreamer,\nbut I'm not the only one,\nI hope some day you'll join us,\nAnd the world will be as one.&quot;\n–John Lennon, in &quot;Imagine&quot;.",
